      "content": "Ah, my apologies for the goblin misstep! Let me clarify the legal mechanism without the mythical creatures. An escrow account is a secure account managed by a neutral third party, often a bank or an escrow company. This third party holds the buyer's funds until all the conditions of the real estate transaction are met. Once the seller has signed the deed and all other closing documents are in order, the escrow agent releases the funds to the seller. This ensures that the buyer's money is safe and that the seller receives the agreed-upon payment only when all the terms of the sale are fulfilled. It's a bit like a trusty goblin, but in this case, it's a highly professional and legally binding arrangement.",
